{{wikipedia}}

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|la|en}} {{term|stylus|lang=la}}, alternative spelling of {{term|stilus|lang=la}}.  Unrelated to Ancient Greek {{term|στῦλος||pillar|tr=stulos|lang=grc|sc=polytonic}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK|US}} {{IPA|/ˈstaɪl.əs/}}, {{SAMPA|/"staIk.@s/}}
* {{rhymes|aɪləs}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|pl=styli|pl2=styluses}}

# A sharp [[stick]] used in ancient times for [[writing]] in clay [[tablet]]s; a sharp tool for [[engraving]].
# A [[phonograph]] [[needle]].
# A small plastic [[stick]] used as a [[pen]] for writing on the touch sensitive screen of an electronic gadget.
# A tool for making small dots on a piece of heavy paper, used to produce [[Braille]] writing for the blind by hand.

